"{\"uid\": \"connexionfrance.com-news-go-ahead-for-electric-flying-taxis-during-paris-olympics-668365\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Subscribe to The Connexion  See prices & plans  HELP GUIDES  Income Tax in France  Healthcare in France  Inheritance Law and Wills in France  Visas and residency cards for France  Subscribe to The Connexion  See prices & plans  HELP GUIDES  Income Tax in France  Healthcare in France  Inheritance Law and Wills in France  Visas and residency cards for France        Flying taxis will take to the skies during the Paris Olympics, it has been confirmed, after the Transport Ministry authorised the creation of a helipad on the Seine - but the journeys will not be paid.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 75, \"end\": 81, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.014690894664115e-27, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 97, \"end\": 103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.014690894664115e-27, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 134, \"end\": 140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.014690894664115e-27, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 172, \"end\": 178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.014690894664115e-27, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 255, \"end\": 261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.014690894664115e-27, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 277, \"end\": 283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.014690894664115e-27, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.014690894664115e-27, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 525, \"end\": 530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.166561363009481e-12, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The government this week authorised the installation of a floating helipad - a temporary barge - on the Seine river, which will serve as a taking off and landing site for VoloCity helicopters.\", \"from\": 569, \"to\": 761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 673, \"end\": 678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.166561363009481e-12, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Created by the German start-up Volocopter, and brought to France by the ADP Group (which runs Paris' airports) and transport company RATP, the taxi company has long been pushing to bring its 'flying taxis' to the Olympics.\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.7774288537736384, \"rank\": 0.28618082172614584, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 794, \"end\": 804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volocopter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Volocopter\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volocopter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volocopter\"}, {\"begin\": 821, \"end\": 827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.014690894664115e-27, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 835, \"end\": 838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adenosine_diphosphate\", \"score\": 0.7478727861437996, \"rank\": 0.31563021825759696, \"text\": \"ADP\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adenosine_diphosphate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adenosine_diphosphate\"}, {\"begin\": 857, \"end\": 862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9782376856454215e-31, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read also:Flying 'drone taxis' on track to carry passengers at Paris Olympics  Now, with just two weeks to go until the Olympics begin (on July 26), the taxis have been authorised to fly between:  Issy-les-Moulineaux and Paris-Austerlitz  The Saint-Cyr-l'\\u00c9cole a\\u00e9rodrome, and the airports of Le Bourget and Roissy-CDG.\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1208, \"end\": 1224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris-Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\"}, {\"begin\": 1279, \"end\": 1289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Air_Show\", \"score\": 0.9999088546618249, \"rank\": 9.115364636489403e-05, \"text\": \"Le Bourget\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Air_Show\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Air_Show\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read also:Flying taxi successfully tested in Paris ahead of 2024 Olympics  However, the group has not received authorisation from the European Union Aviation Safety Agency (EASA) nor the French civil aviation authority la Direction g\\u00e9n\\u00e9rale de l'Aviation civile (DGAC) to take paying passengers during this time.\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1352, \"end\": 1357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9782376856454215e-31, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1450, \"end\": 1455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.893982484857851e-13, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1480, \"end\": 1484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union_Aviation_Safety_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.987434440009016e-48, \"text\": \"EASA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union_Aviation_Safety_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Union_Aviation_Safety_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 1494, \"end\": 1500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.313246471064703e-15, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1570, \"end\": 1574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Directorate_General_for_Civil_Aviation_(France)\", \"score\": 0.948067199056497, \"rank\": 0.021193092621665445, \"text\": \"DGAC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Directorate_General_for_Civil_Aviation_(France)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Directorate_General_for_Civil_Aviation_(France)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This means that only 'demonstration flights' will be allowed during the Olympics, and the flying taxi scheme is still being dubbed 'an experiment'.\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The hours of operation will be limited to between 08:00 and 17:00.\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The number of flights will be capped at two per hour, and 900 flights total during the experiment.\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1935, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"VoloCity will not be able to charge passengers until after December 31, 2024 at the earliest, the government decree states.\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 2060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some ministers in Paris have criticised the government's authorisation of the scheme, calling it an \\\"ecological aberration\\\".\", \"from\": 2062, \"to\": 2186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2080, \"end\": 2085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9782376856454215e-31, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Mairie of Paris is even considering legal action against the decree.\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2201, \"end\": 2206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9782376856454215e-31, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Val\\u00e9rie P\\u00e9cresse, President of the \\u00cele-de-France region, is in support of the project.\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2270, \"end\": 2286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Val\\u00e9rie_P\\u00e9cresse\", \"score\": 0.9999999950741767, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Val\\u00e9rie P\\u00e9cresse\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Val\\u00e9rie_P\\u00e9cresse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Val\\u00e9rie_P\\u00e9cresse\"}, {\"begin\": 2305, \"end\": 2318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_European_Parliament_election_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.870571323944047e-14, \"text\": \"\\u00cele-de-France\", \"types\": [\"Q40231\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_European_Parliament_election_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_European_Parliament_election_in_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is a very good thing that this experiment can go ahead,\\\" she toldLe Figaro.\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The VoloCity helicopters have a futuristic appearance, with a white body and circular loop where a helicopter's blade usually sits.\", \"from\": 2438, \"to\": 2569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are powered by electricity, and 16 small motors rather than one large blade.\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This makes the helicopter less noisy than a typical vessel.\", \"from\": 2652, \"to\": 2711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The helicopters can carry two passengers including the pilot, flying at 100 kp/h at an altitude of 400-500 metres, with a range of 35 km.\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The company is, however, working on automated helicopters that will fly themselves, and a larger five-seater edition.\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2968, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Le taxi volant VoloCity de l'allemand Volocopter, pr\\u00e9sent\\u00e9 \\u00e0 Pontoise.\", \"from\": 2970, \"to\": 3040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3008, \"end\": 3018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volocopter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Volocopter\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volocopter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volocopter\"}, {\"begin\": 3031, \"end\": 3039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontoise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.651928854224261e-16, \"text\": \"Pontoise\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontoise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pontoise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tests pr\\u00e9vus sur l'a\\u00e9rodrome de Pontoise \\u00e0 partir de juin 2021, dans le cadre d'un programme soutenu par la r\\u00e9gion \\u00cele de France, ADP, la RATPpic.twitter.com/txCCQ9Dpel  In 2020, before the helicopters were even officially tested in France, Ms P\\u00e9cressealready saidthat she hoped the flying taxis could be unveiled for the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3377, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3105, \"end\": 3109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_Agency_for_National_Security\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"dans\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_Agency_for_National_Security\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_Agency_for_National_Security\"}, {\"begin\": 3274, \"end\": 3280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.014690894664115e-27, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This would make Ile-de-France \\\"a reference point for the global market for urban air mobility\\\", she said.\", \"from\": 3378, \"to\": 3483, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the same time, however, transport company RATP predicted that it would not be able to sell public tickets for the flights until 2030.\", \"from\": 3485, \"to\": 3621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other companies to have tested flying taxis, including Airbus, pulled out of the 'Olympics race' completely after realising they would not have their prototypes or aviation authorisation ready in time.\", \"from\": 3623, \"to\": 3824, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The traditional event will this year also pay homage to the Olympics and Paralympics  'It's a wonderful, important and symbolic step,' says the head of the restoration project  The mixture of French and English was aimed at international visitors  Wealthy households must make advance payment before final amounts calculated via spring tax return  Local residents rally to help two well-known traders    A reader writes of his experiences with the company  Station in Brittany will include six ultra-fast charging points  When to buy depends if you want a Nordmann fir, a Norway spruce, or an alternative  Homeowners now have until 2030 to set up the devices  Up to three million distributed sensors provide dangerously low readings  Father Christmas may be known for his present delivery on December 24, but in the east of France, another bearded figure bearing gifts is celebrated much earlier in the month  A useful saying for the festive season when hot cider is served in markets  James Campbell reinvents classic p\\u00e2tisserie creations with a contemporary Japanese twist, all made achievable to the home cook  Jo MacDonald, 59, describes how she monetised her hobby in Gers    Both household electricity and gas bills will increase  Issue now drawing attention at the highest levels  Second-home owners must pay their taxe d'habitation this month  Warm spell comes despite rain in west and north  Vote reverses proposal to lower tax exemption thresholds for self-employed workers    Customers can take home a piece of the capital's iconic UNESCO-listed skyline  Columnist Cynthia Spillman provides some useful advice on getting behind the wheel  Richard and Patricia Romain, both 76, moved from Kent, UK, in 2013 and now live near Carcassonne in Aude  High costs could prove barrier to widespread installation of the technology  The index tracks key areas to 'compare how inequalities affect our lives'  The 108 medicines are considered to pose risks that outweigh the benefits  The new system will help to educate drivers, officials believe  Rules for self-employed workers are different than for employees    Subscribe to The Connexion  See prices & plans  HELP GUIDES  Income Tax in France  Healthcare in France  Inheritance Law and Wills in France  Visas and residency cards for France\", \"from\": 3826, \"to\": 6119, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4294, \"end\": 4302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brittany\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.760276555384494e-14, \"text\": \"Brittany\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brittany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brittany\"}, {\"begin\": 4382, \"end\": 4394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abies_nordmanniana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nordmann fir\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abies_nordmanniana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abies_nordmanniana\"}, {\"begin\": 4398, \"end\": 4411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Picea_abies\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Norway spruce\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Picea_abies\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Picea_abies\"}, {\"begin\": 4650, \"end\": 4656, \"title\": \